# Frontend navigation over modals

When adding a **view** (form, detail, settings subsection, multi-step flow, list drill-in), make it a **navigator-accessible screen/route**, not a modal.

## Prefer

- Flutter: `go_router` / `Navigator.push` routes under `lib/router/` with a clear way **back** (AppBar leading, `context.pop` / `Navigator.pop`, or shell tab).
- React (`user-manager-web`): a real route the user can open, leave, and deep-link when useful.
- The new surface must work in a **navigator context** — never a dead-end with no exit.

## Modals are OK only for

- Confirmations (delete / discard)
- Short information dialogs
- Very simple one-shot forms (e.g. rename, single field)

## Avoid modals for

- Full create/edit flows, multi-section settings, rich detail pages, or anything that needs its own back stack or URL

```dart
// ❌ BAD — non-trivial form as a dialog
showDialog(context: context, builder: (_) => ActivityFormDialog(...));

// ✅ GOOD — push a screen the user can leave
Navigator.of(context).push(
  MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => const ActivityFormScreen()),
);
// or a GoRoute under lib/router/
```
